'''Bastion''' was the code-name to designated a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] as a temporal [[Capital/Legends|capital]] for the [[Imperial Remnant]], and involved establishing a interim base of operations, and the relocation of the [[Council of Moffs/Legends|Council of Moffs]], along with [[Imperial Military/Legends|military assets]] and people to the provisional location.

==History==
During the latter years of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the capital was moved from planet to planet, each temporarily being designated "Bastion". A degree of continuity between these worlds was maintained not just by their serving as successive meeting place of the [[Council of Moffs/Legends|Moff Council]], but also by their role as the Empire's administrative headquarters, home to the state archives removed from Coruscant in [[7 ABY/Legends|7]] or [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]], plus the associated bureaucratic functionaries, and also the site of [[Bastion Military Control]], the central apparatus of the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]].

It is possible that [[Orinda/Legends|Orinda]] and [[Ord Cantrell/Legends|Ord Cantrell]] were early Bastions, but by [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]] the site of the Imperial capital was unknown to the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], and the rogue [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and former [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Alliance Special Forces]] commando [[Dal Konur]] attempted to locate the planet. By [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], the central administration had relocated to [[Bastion/Legends|Sartinaynian]], the capital of [[Braxant sector/Legends|Braxant sector]], which remained the capital of Imperial space for more than a century, and came to adopt the name of Bastion as its own.

